A*STAR's Science and Engineering Research Council (SERC) promotes public sector  research and development in the physical sciences and engineering, which span a  wide range of fields, including advanced manufacturing, chemicals,  communications, computational sciences, data storage, materials, metrology and  microelectronics. Within SERC, the Engineering Cluster promotes R&amp;D and  innovation for Precision Engineering, Aerospace, Marine &amp; Offshore, and  Supply Chain; while Electronics Cluster promotes R&amp;D and innovation for  Semiconductors and Data Systems Technologies.

This  role will support SERC뭩 Engineering and Electronics Cluster officers  administratively in their day-to-day operations. As an illustration,  responsibilities typically include:
     Perform  knowledge management and documentation control
     Administrative  processing of both internal and external communication
     Coordinate  and organize meetings, events and company engagements
     Provide  support to the tasks and activities of the Cluster(s), as required

Job  Requirements
     Minimum  2-5 years of working experience
     Proficiency  in MS Office (in particular, Excel and Word)
     Excellent  time management and multi-tasking capabilities
     Good  stakeholder management
     Attention  to detail, yet have an agile and flexible mindset to enable problem  solving
     A  self-starter, independent, resourceful and able to work in a team